To determine whether NaDC3 induces aging through inhibiting SIRT1 pathway, SIRT1 deacetylase activity was detected by fluorescent assay. The results showed that the activity was down-regulated in the WI38/hNaDC3 group (9256 ± 675), compared with that in the control (20,569 ± 1035) and the WI38/neo groups (18,972 ± 1158) (P
 < 0.05), (Fig. 5
).
